Investigations trying to determine the cause of the blaze. CAPE TOWN – Cape Town authorities have confirmed that three people including two children have died after a fire swept through Vrygrond in Muizenberg this morning. Investigations trying to determine the cause of the blaze. Cape Town Fire and Rescue Theo Layne says, “Just before 4 am this morning the city’s Fire Rescue Services responded Fredrick Road in the Vrygrond Muizenberg area. One adult male and two male minor sustained fatal burns.”